.TH labimp 1 "22.06.26" "labimp" "User Manual"
.SH NAME
\fBlabimp\fR \- import laboratory values from LDT files (QC\-Labmessenger and doc.net) into a MariaDB database
.br
(Deutsche Manpage: \(aqman \-Lde labimp\(aq)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBlabimp\fR [\-<shortopt>|\-\-<longopt> [<argument>]] \&...
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBlabimp\fR reads LDT files produced by laboratory information systems
and stores the contained laboratory findings automatically in a
MariaDB database.
Both the older LDT\-1/2 format (produced e.g. by the
\fIQC\-Labmessenger\fR) and the newer LDT\-3 format (produced by the
laboratory information system \fIdoc.net\fR by Sonic Healthcare Germany)
are supported.
.PP
\fBlabimp\fR is designed to run as a cron job called every minute,
but can also be invoked manually with various options.
.SH INSTALLATION
Prerequisites: MariaDB/MySQL, libtiff, libboost (iostreams, locale),
libacl, ncursesw.
.PP
Build:
.nf
  make
  make install
.fi
.PP
On the first run without a complete configuration file,
\fBlabimp\fR automatically switches to interactive mode and prompts
for all required parameters.
.SH HOW IT WORKS
.SS QC\-Labmessenger (LDT 1/2)
\fBlabimp\fR searches \fBldatvz\fR for LDT files matching the patterns
\fB1b*.ld*\fR, \fB*.ldt\fR, \fBx*.ld*\fR and \fBlabor*.dat\fR.
After importing, each file is moved to \fBfertigvz\fR.
.SS doc.net (LDT 3, Sonic Healthcare Germany)
doc.net deposits new report files in the directory \fBqvz\fR.
On each invocation, \fBlabimp\fR processes any \fB*.ldt\fR files found there
in the following sequence:
.TP 3
1.
The file is \fBmoved\fR to \fBldatvz\fR and \fBrenamed\fR according to the pattern
.br
\fBLabor\fIYYYYMMDD\fB_\fIHHMMSS\fB_\fIseqno\fB.ldt\fR.
.br
Date and time are taken from the field
\fBTimestamp_Erstellung_Datensatz\fR (LDT\-3 codes 8218/7278/7279)
inside the file.
If this timestamp is absent, the file modification date is used.
The sequence number \fIseqno\fR is incremented until the resulting
filename does not yet exist in \fBldatvz\fR.
.TP 3
2.
The file (with its new name) is \fBcopied\fR to up to four configurable
target directories (\fBzvz1\fR\-\fBzvz4\fR).
.TP 3
3.
Any PDF attachment contained in the file (Base64\-encoded in LDT\-3
fields 8242/6329) is \fBextracted\fR to \fBpdfvz\fR as
\fI<filename_without_extension>\fB.pdf\fR.
.TP 3
4.
The LDT\-3 content is internally \fBconverted\fR to an LDT\-1/2\-compatible
format and stored in the database tables, analogously to the
QC\-Labmessenger files.
.PP
.B LDT\-3 field mapping:
Most field codes are identical in LDT 3 and LDT 1/2
(3101 surname, 3102 first name, 3103 date of birth, 3110 sex,
8310/8311 order number/key, 8401 report type,
8410/8411 test identifier/long text, 8420/8421/8422 value/unit/limit,
8460 normal range, 8428/8430 sample material).
Differences:
.TP 16
\fB7278 / 7279\fR
Date (YYYYMMDD) and time (HHMMSS) inside timestamp objects (Obj_0054).
Mapped to 8301 (entry date), 8302/8303 (report date) or
8432/8433 (sampling date/time) depending on context.
.TP 16
\fB3564\fR
Result text in bacteriology blocks → 8480 (comment).
.TP 16
\fB7306\fR
Result status: 01=final, 04=partial, 99=replacement report → 8418.
.TP 16
\fB7305\fR
Order key → 8311.
.TP 16
\fB8239\fR
Laboratory name → 8320.
.TP 16
\fB0001\fR
LDT version string (e.g. \fILDT3.2.19\fR) → 9212.
.SS Patient assignment
After import, \fBlabimp\fR tries to assign the laboratory values to a
patient in the table \fBlaborneu\fR based on name, date of birth,
entry date and measured values (function \fBusmod\fR).
.SS Database tables
All tables carry a configurable prefix (\fBvorsil\fR,
default \fIlabory\fR):
.PP
.TS
l l.
\fI<prefix>dat\fR	imported files
\fI<prefix>saetze\fR	LDT data packets (record headers)
\fI<prefix>aerzte\fR	physician information
\fI<prefix>us\fR	examinations (per patient and order)
\fI<prefix>wert\fR	numeric and text laboratory values
\fI<prefix>bakt\fR	microbiological findings
\fI<prefix>plab\fR	laboratory addresses
\fI<prefix>pneu\fR	long text/unit/group per method
\fI<prefix>pnb\fR	normal ranges
\fI<prefix>parameter\fR	laboratory parameter master data
\fI<prefix>pgl\fR	parameter equalities (synonyms)
\fI<prefix>fehlt\fR	unknown LDT fields
\fI<prefix>hinw\fR	order notes/comments
\fI<prefix>qspez\fR	sample material specifications
\fI<prefix>leist\fR	billing items (EBM/GOÄ)
.TE
